WEBVTT

00:11.640 --> 00:13.507
<i>Authorities have
identified a person of interest</i>

00:13.607 --> 00:17.073
<i>in the mysterious death of
Treasury Official Edward Homm.</i>

00:17.173 --> 00:18.940
That's my Stacy.
Someone's at the door.

00:19.040 --> 00:21.240
The fuck?
I was afraid of that.

00:22.573 --> 00:24.507
Kills a guy with
a fire extinguisher

00:24.607 --> 00:26.740
and suddenly he's in MI5.

00:26.840 --> 00:28.140
- You said he was okay.
- He's fine.

00:28.240 --> 00:30.473
<i>Edward Homm is the story here.</i>

00:30.573 --> 00:32.407
<i>Think about it. Can you think
of one other person</i>

00:32.507 --> 00:34.673
<i>in the last 2,000 years?
My source, Zaius,</i>

00:34.773 --> 00:38.973
<i>said he's gonna get me proof
that Ed is not dead.</i>

00:39.073 --> 00:41.306
Weir didn't kill anybody.
I have proof.

00:41.407 --> 00:44.273
Oh, you figured out the stuff
in the briefcase?

00:44.373 --> 00:47.140
Whoever has this info
controls everything.

00:47.240 --> 00:48.740
- Where are you going?
- To find him.

00:48.840 --> 00:50.073
Maybe he went to his ex-wife's.

00:50.173 --> 00:51.673
I didn't know Weir
even had an ex.

00:51.773 --> 00:52.673
It's really good you came.

00:52.773 --> 00:53.940
It doesn't hurt

00:54.040 --> 00:55.707
to look like
successful co-parents

00:55.807 --> 00:57.007
every once in a while.

00:57.107 --> 00:58.339
Sir?

00:58.440 --> 00:59.673
What's this?

00:59.773 --> 01:00.707
You wouldn't believe me
if I told you.

01:00.807 --> 01:02.107
What can I offer you

01:02.207 --> 01:03.973
to make you forget
this file ever existed?

01:04.073 --> 01:05.440
Oh, I thought you'd never ask.

01:05.540 --> 01:07.607
I'd like to be made
the head of the task force

01:07.707 --> 01:09.073
that's tracking down John Weir.

01:09.173 --> 01:10.473
<i>The Senate majority leader</i>

01:10.573 --> 01:11.740
<i>has called for an immediate vote</i>

01:11.840 --> 01:13.040
<i>on the shared data act.</i>

01:13.140 --> 01:14.473
This wasn't about winning
the presidency.

01:14.573 --> 01:16.940
This was about passing
a piece of legislation

01:17.040 --> 01:18.272
that the senator campaigned on.

01:18.407 --> 01:20.073
And when it does,
Crowley gains access

01:20.173 --> 01:22.973
to thousands of data points
on every single American.

01:23.073 --> 01:25.007
- Your father is using you.
- Liar!

01:28.607 --> 01:31.007
Someone's telling you
what to fucking say?

01:32.140 --> 01:33.840
<i>Hello, John.</i>

01:33.940 --> 01:35.240
Been running
an op on me, Dad?

01:35.407 --> 01:36.507
Jesus Christ!

01:36.607 --> 01:38.707
Crowley wants no loose ends

01:38.807 --> 01:40.007
in the Homm operation.

01:40.107 --> 01:41.873
He just fucking
outplayed me, John.

01:41.973 --> 01:43.007
I'm so sorry.

01:43.107 --> 01:44.773
No more apologizing.

01:44.873 --> 01:47.073
Just tell me that
we're gonna work together

01:47.173 --> 01:50.873
to stop this motherfucker
once and for all.

01:56.407 --> 01:58.473
Another week? Seriously?

01:58.573 --> 02:00.607
You were supposed to be done
a month ago.

02:02.040 --> 02:04.407
Yeah, but what about my job,
my career?

02:05.607 --> 02:08.407
I know things happen,
but I mean...

02:09.440 --> 02:12.807
We can talk about this when
you're back, whenever that is.

02:12.907 --> 02:14.272
It's giving me a headache

02:14.407 --> 02:17.407
and that is the last thing
I need right now.

02:40.640 --> 02:41.807
