04:43.673 --> 04:45.540
<i>A bizarre scene
in Washington, D.C.</i>

04:45.640 --> 04:48.507
<i>as three federal judges on
the prestigious D.C. circuit</i>

04:48.607 --> 04:50.773
<i>have died or been killed
in a single day.</i>

04:50.873 --> 04:53.673
<i>None of the cases
seem to be connected,</i>

04:53.773 --> 04:55.306
<i>but the D.C. circuit court</i>

04:55.407 --> 04:56.773
<i>has been shut indefinitely</i>

04:56.873 --> 04:57.940
<i>- for fear of further violence.</i>
- It's begun.

04:58.040 --> 04:59.607
Crowley?
- Yeah.

04:59.707 --> 05:03.007
It's like the most
powerful court in the country.

05:03.106 --> 05:04.807
Crowley's just shut it down.

05:04.907 --> 05:07.840
Then he'll probably pack it
full of his own people,

05:07.940 --> 05:09.306
or just not reopen it again.

05:09.407 --> 05:11.206
He-He's taking over.

05:11.306 --> 05:14.573
He paralyzes the courts,
then what?

05:15.440 --> 05:19.473
We were in, uh, in India,
in Mumbai, once.

05:20.239 --> 05:22.440
We were looking out
over the slums.

05:23.640 --> 05:27.540
And he said, "They should all be
put down like rabid dogs."

05:28.440 --> 05:30.807
Then he said, "The one thing
this country has got right

05:30.907 --> 05:32.407
is the caste system."

05:32.407 --> 05:35.740
Uh, "People know their place
and they're kept there."

05:37.239 --> 05:40.272
He'll build the country
he's always wanted.

05:40.407 --> 05:43.139
Ruled over by a privileged few.

05:43.239 --> 05:45.072
He'll create
a permanent underclass,

05:45.172 --> 05:47.072
women in the home,

05:47.172 --> 05:49.540
homosexuals in the closet.

05:49.640 --> 05:53.106
Or, better still,
buried in the ground.

05:54.407 --> 05:57.039
It's the world
of a hundred years ago.

05:57.139 --> 05:59.172
His world.

06:00.172 --> 06:02.272
God help us all.

06:06.172 --> 06:07.607
Let's talk about next steps.

06:07.707 --> 06:10.873
We have documented
proof of a conspiracy.

06:10.972 --> 06:14.573
It-It's bigger than
the Pentagon Papers,

06:14.673 --> 06:16.172
Panama Papers, Pandora Papers.

06:16.272 --> 06:18.006
I could build
a bulletproof case on this.

06:18.106 --> 06:19.006
Anyone could.

06:19.106 --> 06:20.773
Can we just go public?

06:20.873 --> 06:22.239
Well, hardly.

06:22.407 --> 06:24.740
Right now, Crowley controls
the narrative.

06:24.840 --> 06:27.306
You know, he's got the media
blabbing nonstop

06:27.407 --> 06:29.773
about the Evers assassination
and dead judges.

06:29.873 --> 06:33.306
And he'll use fear
to turn public opinion

06:33.407 --> 06:34.940
against whatever
we throw out there.

06:35.039 --> 06:37.139
He's right. We have to control
the narrative first.

06:37.239 --> 06:38.239
Then we can reach out
to specific journalists.

06:38.407 --> 06:39.540
I've got some ideas about that.

06:39.640 --> 06:41.773
Isn't it too late?
There's a window.

06:41.873 --> 06:44.239
But it's closing. Which is why
I think, for maximum exposure,

06:44.407 --> 06:46.239
we need to move over
to the Homm Plan.

06:46.407 --> 06:49.106
Um, Homm-- Homm Plan?

06:49.206 --> 06:50.707
There's a Homm Plan?

06:50.807 --> 06:52.407
Of course, are you blind?
There's a Homm Plan.

06:52.407 --> 06:54.473
And it's pretty simple.

06:54.573 --> 06:57.407
We reveal that you're alive,
it'll go viral.

06:57.407 --> 06:58.840
At which point, the public

06:58.939 --> 07:00.840
controls the narrative.
We move in from there.

07:00.939 --> 07:02.939
The bread crumbs we've been
throwing out to Morgan Shaw

07:03.039 --> 07:05.507
will pay off in a viral moment.

07:05.607 --> 07:06.907
You're... You're Zaius?

07:07.006 --> 07:09.072
It's much easier to create
a folk hero now

07:09.172 --> 07:10.239
than it was back in the day.

07:10.407 --> 07:11.272
Hold on.

07:11.407 --> 07:14.407
"Ed Is Not Dead" is you two?

07:14.507 --> 07:15.972
I-I thought that was--

07:16.072 --> 07:17.407
Just post something on Reddit

07:17.407 --> 07:18.972
and buy likes from
a Filipino click farm,

07:19.072 --> 07:20.939
and bingo, people are in love.

07:21.039 --> 07:23.206
"Click farm."

07:24.072 --> 07:25.473
Are you serious?

07:47.039 --> 07:49.072
I don't even know.

07:49.172 --> 07:51.206
So that's...

07:51.306 --> 07:52.640
Debra.

07:52.740 --> 07:55.039
And that's...
Uh, just give me one, just...

07:55.139 --> 07:56.507
Just wait a-a minute.

07:56.607 --> 07:57.972
Uh-uh.

07:58.072 --> 07:59.507
What?

07:59.607 --> 08:02.407
You got a bizarre message
in your public account.

08:02.407 --> 08:05.306
I... thought it was
typical wingnut bullshit,

08:05.407 --> 08:06.972
but, uh, it said...

08:08.039 --> 08:09.206
Okay, first thing...

08:09.306 --> 08:11.239
Spit. Spit it out.

08:11.407 --> 08:13.906
Sorry. I...

08:15.172 --> 08:17.272
There was an attachment.

08:23.239 --> 08:24.473
She's in. Wow.

08:24.573 --> 08:26.106
Briar Park Grill, 8:00 a.m.

08:26.206 --> 08:29.707
There's only one thing that
worries me about this plan.

08:29.807 --> 08:31.407
It doesn't end
with Crowley's death.

08:31.407 --> 08:33.707
And that's the only way
to stop him.

08:34.640 --> 08:36.707
Dad. You have to trust me.

08:36.807 --> 08:38.407
I know it's not a big thing
in our family,

08:38.507 --> 08:41.172
but we don't have a choice.
This is gonna work.

08:41.272 --> 08:44.306
Hmm. Okay.

08:46.740 --> 08:48.239
"Okay"?

08:49.607 --> 08:50.939
Wow.

08:54.206 --> 08:56.707
You should get some sleep.

08:58.206 --> 08:59.972
Yeah.

09:02.006 --> 09:03.673
You, too.

09:06.906 --> 09:08.640
Weir...

09:14.407 --> 09:16.440
Um...

09:22.473 --> 09:24.440
You had me worried.

09:24.540 --> 09:27.139
I was...
I was worried about you.

09:27.239 --> 09:28.906
I know. I'm sorry.

09:29.006 --> 09:30.306
I get it.

09:30.407 --> 09:33.072
No, no, I-I don't think you do.

09:33.172 --> 09:36.906
Look, I-I wasn't trying
to be cute, okay,

09:37.006 --> 09:38.607
putting you on the bus.

09:38.707 --> 09:40.139
What we're doing right now
is dangerous

09:40.239 --> 09:42.306
and I was trying to protect you.

09:42.407 --> 09:44.106
This work, um...

09:44.206 --> 09:45.839
I'm gonna be honest, it...

09:45.939 --> 09:47.172
it's cost me everything.

09:47.272 --> 09:50.507
And I mean... everything.

09:52.906 --> 09:54.407
Like your friends?

09:54.407 --> 09:56.607
Valence?

09:57.407 --> 09:59.306
Yeah.

09:59.407 --> 10:01.373
Your wife?

10:01.473 --> 10:04.906
What... What happened with her?

10:11.507 --> 10:13.006
A job went wrong.

10:13.106 --> 10:15.573
I fucked up, she got hurt.

10:15.673 --> 10:18.039
Caught in the middle.

10:19.440 --> 10:21.573
And then she left.

10:25.540 --> 10:27.872
You still love her?

10:32.607 --> 10:36.039
Hailey, I think you know
how I feel about you.

10:36.139 --> 10:37.473
Yeah.

10:37.573 --> 10:39.407
Well, let's face it,
I'm not the most...

10:39.507 --> 10:41.239
...stable guy, so...

10:41.339 --> 10:43.039
No.

10:44.039 --> 10:47.540
I don't think I could handle
losing someone like you.

10:50.373 --> 10:52.772
I know I couldn't handle it.

11:07.139 --> 11:09.972
I went to Jo Madi.

11:10.072 --> 11:11.739
What?

11:11.839 --> 11:15.806
I... I-I was worried, I-I...

11:15.906 --> 11:18.206
You were out of your mind,
you were...

11:18.306 --> 11:23.139
I figured an arrested John Weir
was an alive John Weir.

11:24.407 --> 11:27.739
You said Jo Madi was honest.

11:27.839 --> 11:29.407
So I...

11:29.407 --> 11:31.906
I gave her some information

11:32.006 --> 11:35.272
to-to prove
what was going on and...

11:35.407 --> 11:38.972
and I-I asked her
to arrest you.

11:39.072 --> 11:42.806
To take you off the street
so that you could be safe.

12:01.272 --> 12:02.573
Okay.

12:06.906 --> 12:08.139
Okay?

12:10.407 --> 12:12.239
Yeah, okay.

12:12.407 --> 12:16.139
I mean, I... I get it.

12:16.239 --> 12:19.872
You thought you had one shot
to protect me and you took it.

12:19.972 --> 12:23.407
Okay.

12:23.507 --> 12:27.206
You did it because...

12:31.272 --> 12:33.006
Yeah.

12:33.106 --> 12:35.172
Yeah?

12:35.272 --> 12:36.939
Yeah.
- Yeah.

